{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"type":"conformsTo"}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudsswitchitem"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem"},"abstract":[{"text":"Switch item is a UI element that allows to toggle between two states, typically “On” and “Off”, and used to enable or disable features, options or settings.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Switch Item covers a wider range of contexts by allowing to toggle the visibility of additional text labels and icon assets.","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"struct","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSSwitchItem"}],"title":"OUDSSwitchItem","externalID":"s:14OUDSComponents14OUDSSwitchItemV","platforms":[{"deprecated":false,"introducedAt":"15.0","name":"iOS","unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"macOS","unavailable":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"13.0","deprecated":false},{"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"16.0","beta":false,"name":"tvOS","deprecated":false},{"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"introducedAt":"1.0","unavailable":false,"name":"visionOS"},{"deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"introducedAt":"11.0","name":"watchOS","beta":false}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"OUDSSwitchItem","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Structure","modules":[{"name":"Components"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSSwitchItem"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"],"kind":"mentions"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Layouts","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Layouts"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component can be rendered as two different layouts:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"default","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": the component has a leading indicator, a label and optional texts, and an optional trailing decorative icon","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"inverse","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": like the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"default","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" layout but with a trailing switch indicator and a leading optional decorative icon","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Indicator states","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Indicator-states"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The switch indicator has two available states set as a boolean property that determines whether the toggle is on or off.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Particular cases","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Particular-cases"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" can be related to an error situation, for example troubles for a formular.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A dedicated look and feel is implemented for that if the ","type":"text"},{"code":"isError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" flag is risen.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In that case if the component displayed an icon, this icon will be replaced automatically by an error icon.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In addition, the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem"},{"text":" can be in read only mode, i.e. the user cannot interact with the component yet but this component must not be considered","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as disabled.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The switch can be also outlined in some cases.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Accessibility considerations","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Accessibility-considerations"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Voice Over"}]},{"type":"text","text":" will use several elements to describe the component: if component disabled \/ read only, if error context, the label and optional texts and a custom switch trait."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Forbidden-by-design","text":"Forbidden by design"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a read only component.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a disabled component.","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The design system does not allow to have both a read only and a disabled component."}],"type":"strong"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Code-samples","text":"Code samples"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["    \/\/ Supposing we have an unselected state","    @Published var isOn: Bool = false","","    \/\/ A leading switch with a label.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $isOn)","","    \/\/ Localizable from bundle can also be used","    OUDSSwitchItem(LocalizedStringKey(\"notifications_setting\"), bundle: Bundle.module, isOn: $isOn)","","    \/\/ A leading switch with a label, but in read only mode (user cannot interact yet, but not disabled).","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $isOn, isReadOnly: true)","","    \/\/ A leading switch with a label, and a description text.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $isOn, description: \"The Beatles\")","","    \/\/ A leading switch with an additional label.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $isOn, description: \"The Beatles\")","","    \/\/ A trailing switch with a label, an additional label, a description text and an icon.","    \/\/ The inverse layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\",","                   isOn: $isOn,","                   description: \"The Beatles\",","                   isReversed: true,","                   icon: Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\"))","","    \/\/ A trailing switch with a label, a description text, an icon, a divider and is about an error.","    \/\/ The inverse layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Rescue from this world!\",","                   isOn: $isOn,","                   description: \"Put your hand in mine\",","                   icon: Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\"),","                   isReversed: true,","                   isError: true,","                   hasDivider: true)","","    \/\/ If on error, add an error message can help user to understand error context","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Rescue from this world!\",","                   isOn: $isOn,","                   isError: true,","                   errorText: \"Something wrong\",","                   hasDivider: true)","","    \/\/ A leading switch with a label, but disabled.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Rescue from this world!\", isOn: $isOn)","        .disabled(true)","","    \/\/ Never disable a read only or an error-related switch as it will crash","    \/\/ This is forbidden by design!","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Kaboom!\", isOn: $isOn, isError: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Kaboom!\", isOn: $isOn, isReadOnly: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you need to flip your icon depending to the layout direction or not (e.g. if RTL mode lose semantics  \/ meanings):","type":"text"}]},{"code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSSwitchItem(\"Lucy in the Sky with Diamonds\", isOn: $isOn, flipLeadingIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Design documentation","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Design-documentation"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-switch","isActive":true}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Themes rendering","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Themes-rendering"},{"text":"Orange","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Orange"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_switchItem_Orange"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Orange Compact","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Orange-Compact"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_switchItem_OrangeCompact"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Sosh","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Sosh"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_switchItem_Sosh","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Wireframe","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Wireframe"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_switchItem_Wireframe","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"1.5.0 (Figma component design version)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Version"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"0.14.0","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Since"}]}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem\/init(_:isOn:description:icon:flipIcon:isReversed:isError:errorText:isReadOnly:hasDivider:constrainedMaxWidth:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem\/init(_:tableName:bundle:isOn:description:icon:flipIcon:isReversed:isError:errorText:isReadOnly:hasDivider:constrainedMaxWidth:)"],"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem\/body"]},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem\/View-Implementations","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSSwitchItem\/View-Implementations"],"generated":true,"title":"Default Implementations"}],"references":{"doc://OUDSComponents/documentation/OUDSComponents/OUDSSwitchItem/init(_:tableName:bundle:isOn:description:icon:flipIcon:isReversed:isError:errorText:isReadOnly:hasDivider:constrainedMaxWidth:)":{"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Creates a switch with a localized label, looking up the key in the given bundle.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:7SwiftUI18LocalizedStringKeyV","text":"LocalizedStringKey"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"tableName"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"kind":"extern